TEUM Connect the dots fellas Devicescape was partnered with iPASS when iPASS cut a deal with Citrix back in 2015 In 2018 along came Pareteum and paid 3MM to use iPASS software In late 2018 iPASS was about to be delisted fold its tent and disappear Citrix and Pareteum relied on iPASS software what would happen to both if the software was no longer supported So Pareteum had little choice but to scoop up iPASS and then had the gall to announce they were doing a big deal with Citrix Citrix already had a deal with iPASS and was part and parcel to the acquisition by Pareteum There was no NEW DEAL worth lots of cash It was a part of a deal they acquired a deal to buy a firm that was FAILING even with Citrix in the fold
